    "narrative": "For today\u2019s slate, **Jos\u00e9 Ram\u00edrez** is our clear priority play. With a commanding score of 84.25, he draws an favorable matchup against Mart\u00edn P\u00e9rez, buoyed by strong SP skill indicators and a prime #3 spot in the order. He is the anchor of our lineup, providing the highest floor and ceiling as we hunt for counting stats. **Lawrence Butler** also grades out exceptionally well at 73.47; despite the park factor drag, his elite #1 spot in the order combined with a favorable matchup against Senga makes him a high-efficiency choice for runs and potential stolen bases. Both **Will Smith** (71.86) and **Bryson Stott** (69.44) are strong starts as well, with the latter benefiting from a +13% dynamic platoon edge that keeps his production potential high despite a mid-tier opponent in Pfaadt.\n\nThe decision to bench **Wenceel Perez** was the most difficult call of the day. His score of 52.66 reflects solid underlying metrics and potential for stolen base upside given the slow delivery of the opposing pitcher, yet he failed to eclipse the efficiency scores of our primary outfielders or middle infielders. **Taylor Ward** was also considered, but his projected matchup against the elite Logan Webb (3.14 xERA) significantly hampered his outlook, keeping him on the pine. We are monitoring the status of **Cal Raleigh**, **Will Smith**, **Luis Arraez**, **Tyler Freeman**, **Matt Chapman**, **Jung Hoo Lee**, **Brendan Donovan**, and **Gavin Sheets**, as all remain \"Lineup Pending.\" While we have modeled them in their historical spots, any significant shift down in the batting order would compress their efficiency scores and potentially necessitate a roster adjustment to protect our daily game caps.",
